cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with output prediction for bilinear systems, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a reinforcement learning scheme for selecting the most appropriate prediction model, which falls under the scope of machine learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The use of reinforcement learning for model selection also falls under the scope of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): The paper may also fall under the scope of software engineering, as it proposes a supervisory scheme for automating the process of selecting the most appropriate prediction model during runtime. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The simulation of temperature prediction in residential buildings may also fall under the scope of computational engineering.
